Description:
A "Uniswap number" can refer to two main things: a number, which is a sequential identifier for each block in a Uniswap (also called [block height](https://www.google.com/search?sca_esv=d8b03bc1a9f4816e&biw=1536&bih=695&q=block+height&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjI5c-1yZKRAxUXpIkEHf0bFCQQxccNegQIHRAB&mstk=AUtExfDKzW2nUGuOvuPFCccw0YIv3_6Nd9OYJul4oOXrqqs39xy0SSJa2vNjgRW57PUwX-0-sP3bL240nCPz4Bf-kEVYpkIL2x8c9carpPJb62hUHjw95_NrdAhyEXG-iZwRVZk&csui=3)), or a Uniswap address, which is a unique identifier used to send and receive cryptocurrency. Block numbers are sequential, starting from 0, and identify a specific block's position, while a Uniswap address is a unique identifier similar to a bank account number.

Uniswap Labs does not provide customer support via a contact number. As a decentralized protocol, official support is primarily offered through a dedicated help center and email address. Official support channels for Uniswap Labs are: Help Center: support.uniswap.org Support Email: email address removed for privacy reasons Submit a Request: You can fill out a support form directly via their Help Center. Discord: Join the official Uniswap Discord server for community and developer discussions.
